---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="General Information"
  description="Regulatory and general information about Windeatts Solicitors LLP, including SRA registration details."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'General Information' }]}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-headings:font-(family-name:--font-heading) prose-headings:text-navy">
      <h2>About Our Firm</h2>
      <p>
        Windeatts LLP is a Limited Liability Partnership registered in England and Wales with
        registered number OC382943. Our registered office is at 20 Fore Street, Kingsbridge,
        Devon TQ7 1NY.
      </p>

      <h2>Regulation</h2>
      <p>
        Windeatts LLP is authorised and regulated by the Solicitors Regulation Authority (SRA).
        Our SRA number is 636433. You can verify our registration on the
        <a href="https://www.sra.org.uk/consumers/register/organisation/?sraNumber=636433" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SRA website</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>VAT</h2>
      <p>Our VAT registration number is 141 4088 92.</p>

      <h2>Professional Indemnity Insurance</h2>
      <p>
        We maintain professional indemnity insurance in accordance with the requirements of the
        Solicitors Regulation Authority. Details of our insurers are available on request.
      </p>

      <h2>Equality and Diversity</h2>
      <p>
        Windeatts LLP is committed to promoting equality and diversity in all of its dealings
        with clients, third parties and employees. We aim to provide a legal service that is
        accessible to all.
      </p>

      <h2>Interest Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We hold client money in accordance with the SRA Accounts Rules. Where we hold client
        funds on which interest is earned, we will account to you for that interest in accordance
        with our interest policy. Details are available on request.
      </p>

      <h2>Money Laundering</h2>
      <p>
        We are required by law to verify the identity of our clients and to report any suspicious
        activity to the National Crime Agency. We may therefore ask you to provide identification
        documents before we can act for you. We appreciate your understanding and cooperation in
        this regard.
      </p>

      <h2>Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        We are committed to providing a high-quality legal service. If you are unhappy with any
        aspect of our service, please see our
        <a href="/complaints">complaints procedure</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Third Party Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Unless otherwise agreed in writing, we do not accept responsibility to anyone other than
        our client for the advice we give. Our terms of business contain a more detailed statement
        of the basis on which we provide our services.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
